									</div>
									<br>
									<i>MAEESTRO</i> is a proof of concept realized during my Bachelor's internsheep at Aicas, which aims to run Android code on any Java Virtual Machine.
									The idea came from the chance to use a JVM for embedded device, the Jamaica Car Virtual Machine, and it was very exiting to have car devices
									able to run the same app that you have in your smartphone.<br>
									It is able to run many different types of apps, including widgets and simple games too, in different resolutions and screen orientation.
									<p>
									<i class="fa fa-android"> </i> Check out the project <a href="https://github.com/ammirate/android-wrapper" target="_blank">here</a>!
